01:50.600 --> 01:57.440
So yeah, I give this idea of a mode of being,

01:57.440 --> 02:01.240
borrowing this from the phenomenologists, of course,

02:01.240 --> 02:02.880
this kind of term.

02:02.880 --> 02:05.360
But I use it a bit differently in the book.

02:05.360 --> 02:13.120
And this is the idea that one's particular use of language

02:13.120 --> 02:17.840
in order to compensate for the inherent schism

02:17.880 --> 02:23.800
between the inner world and the humanized world

02:23.800 --> 02:25.720
is, for me, a mode of being.

02:25.720 --> 02:27.760
It is a mode of existence.

02:27.760 --> 02:30.360
Because we find our existence in language,

02:30.360 --> 02:33.920
as you were saying and you were quoting from the book.

02:33.920 --> 02:38.040
One is does not only find their meaning,

02:38.040 --> 02:43.840
let's say, in this kind of Satrian way,

02:43.840 --> 02:48.320
existence prior to meaning that you are born

02:48.320 --> 02:55.160
and then you find who you are or whatever your goals or aims

02:55.160 --> 02:57.160
are at your life.

02:57.160 --> 03:00.400
We see with you is this expert that you brought,

03:00.400 --> 03:04.560
is that one is born already endowed with meaning,

03:04.560 --> 03:08.000
already determined by language.

03:08.000 --> 03:10.440
And we say it's a name.

03:10.440 --> 03:13.520
It's these projections that the parents might have on a baby,

03:13.520 --> 03:15.840
even before it is born.

03:15.840 --> 03:20.800
Today, we have the sonogram and these images of the baby

03:20.800 --> 03:21.760
and the womb.

03:21.760 --> 03:24.120
People already start having their fantasies

03:24.120 --> 03:27.880
about even their face structure.

03:27.880 --> 03:30.400
We know if they're a boy or a girl,

03:30.400 --> 03:34.880
one has already meanings that are stuck to them

03:34.880 --> 03:35.760
before they're born.

03:36.600 --> 03:45.840
And so we say one becomes human, one subjectifies,

03:45.840 --> 03:51.360
one is situated in the humanized world

03:51.360 --> 03:54.640
through their use of language, through their relationship

03:54.640 --> 03:57.920
with this language that is alien, that is outside of them,

03:57.920 --> 04:02.480
that exists prior and will exist after.

04:02.480 --> 04:04.320
Now, this particular use of language

04:04.320 --> 04:07.280
is a mode of existence because it situates us

04:07.280 --> 04:11.600
in the world, in the social world, in our body,

04:11.600 --> 04:15.080
in relationship with other people in the world,

04:15.080 --> 04:18.040
in relationship with our own ego.

04:18.040 --> 04:25.120
So language is the mode through which one becomes.

04:25.120 --> 04:30.000
And then neurosis is one of these modes.

04:30.000 --> 04:33.560
And I argue that psychosis and perversion

04:33.560 --> 04:36.080
are also these modes.

04:36.080 --> 04:39.560
But my point is, and this is where

04:39.560 --> 04:43.240
I think maybe this mode of being steps away

04:43.240 --> 04:47.920
from the Heideggerian design, this mode of being

04:47.920 --> 04:54.000
that Heidegger speaks about, is that I'll be a little blunt.

04:54.000 --> 05:00.960
For me, everyone is developmentally disordered.

05:00.960 --> 05:04.000
They say that autism is a developmental disorder.

05:04.000 --> 05:06.920
This is how it's determined.

05:06.920 --> 05:10.360
If you follow Freud, everyone is necessarily

05:10.360 --> 05:12.960
developmentally disordered.

05:12.960 --> 05:16.240
Freud speaks about the fixation of the drives.

05:16.240 --> 05:20.000
So the drives are these things that determine our pleasure

05:20.000 --> 05:20.760
and suffering.

05:20.760 --> 05:23.120
And he says that at a certain point in one's life,

05:23.120 --> 05:26.200
they're fixated, and they stop developing,

05:26.200 --> 05:27.880
uses these words.

05:27.880 --> 05:30.120
They are stopped in the middle of their development.

05:30.120 --> 05:33.160
And then they continue in the same way,

05:33.160 --> 05:34.560
which is not the proper way.

05:34.560 --> 05:37.600
It is just a way that keeps on functioning.

05:37.600 --> 05:41.320
So everyone is, in a sense, developmentally disordered.

05:41.320 --> 05:46.120
We are born split with this inherent schism that

05:46.120 --> 05:47.960
is unmendable.

05:47.960 --> 05:50.680
We use language to compensate for it.

05:50.680 --> 05:56.880
And as we do something in the development of the drives,

05:56.880 --> 06:00.680
of these things that move us, that color the world,

06:00.680 --> 06:04.840
that make the world, basically, objects

06:04.840 --> 06:08.680
exist in the world when they are invested with libido.

06:08.680 --> 06:10.880
They don't exist when they are not invested.

06:10.880 --> 06:14.960
So basically, this means that the world stops developing,

06:14.960 --> 06:16.560
in this sense.

06:16.560 --> 06:20.080
So everyone, the neurotic, the psychotic, the perverse,

06:20.120 --> 06:23.600
and the autistic are all developmentally disordered.

06:23.600 --> 06:26.320
And this is why each of these perspectives

06:26.320 --> 06:28.440
are, let's say, a mode of being.

06:28.440 --> 06:31.360
They're an attitude in relation to reality.

06:31.360 --> 06:36.080
They're a way to do with language.

06:36.080 --> 06:38.880
When I say then that they are distinct,

06:38.880 --> 06:44.280
then I don't make here some kind of an ontological argument.

06:44.280 --> 06:46.720
And this is something that's important to clarify.

06:46.720 --> 06:49.800
I don't mean that here's Woody Allen.

06:49.800 --> 06:51.560
He's neurotic.

06:51.560 --> 06:54.680
Here's Daniel Schreber for its case.

06:54.680 --> 06:56.200
He's psychotic.

06:56.200 --> 07:00.040
And here's, I don't know, Temple Grandin.

07:00.040 --> 07:02.360
She's autistic.

07:02.360 --> 07:09.400
I mean that there are different ways to do with language.

07:09.400 --> 07:20.280
And these necessitate our attention as analysts.

07:20.280 --> 07:24.520
And it means that working with this particular subject that

07:24.520 --> 07:27.800
has this particular way of doing with language

07:27.800 --> 07:31.400
will dictate situating myself in the transference

07:31.400 --> 07:35.200
in such and such a way, and making such and such

07:35.200 --> 07:36.440
interventions.

07:36.440 --> 07:40.600
And with the psychotic subject, that will not be the case.

07:40.600 --> 07:44.160
Because if I will position myself in the same way,

07:44.160 --> 07:46.160
that could be catastrophic.

07:46.160 --> 07:50.040
For instance, this is something, again,

07:50.040 --> 07:52.640
it's not a real example, it's just to clarify my point.

07:52.640 --> 07:57.400
So with neurotic, it's important not to answer one's

07:57.400 --> 07:59.440
demands for love many times.

07:59.440 --> 08:04.040
And this also means that you sometimes go on vacation

08:04.040 --> 08:07.920
and you don't really say, look, I'm sorry,

08:07.920 --> 08:11.160
but I have to go and continue.

08:11.160 --> 08:12.200
You say, I'm going.

08:12.200 --> 08:14.280
We see each other in two weeks.

08:14.280 --> 08:15.480
Let's set a date.

